               <msContents>
                  <summary>1) Ff. 5a-28b: Rite for the Clothing of Monks (and Nuns - the alternate prayers for them are found in their places) with the  Holy Habit [Ser'ata mankosat ba-askima qedus (sic)]. Attributed to James of Sarug (interline addition, f. 5a). 
                     
                     2) Ff. 30a-43b : The Book of the Pearl [Mashafa bahrey], "that is,  the Book of the Lamp" [Mashafa qandil], A ritual for the sick. 
                     
                     3) Ff. 43b-53b: Penitential Ritual [Mashafa qeder], for one "who has denied his faith or has defiled his body with an unbeliever". 
                     
                     4) Ff. 54a-63b : Marriage Ritual [Mashafa taklil]. 
                     
                     5) F. 63 b: Prayer to be recited over the child 7 days after his birth to give him his name. </summary>
               </msContents>
